

1. Bayesian Optimization by Roman Garnett (UW-SL).
  an OS book for free online, github is https://github.com/bayesoptbook/bayesoptbook.github.io 

2. CS 281 from Harvard Course Site shares many good books, in particular the series by Murphy (books 1 and 2 free online)
  CS 281: https://groups.seas.harvard.edu/courses/cs281/#books 
  Murphy's books: https://probml.github.io/pml-book/

3. I have a hard copy of Machine Learning: A Bayesian and Optimization Perspective by Theodoridis, it is not OS however and no pdfs online
  good.
